Automation:
============
Prerequisties:
Install intelij

1. Design and create an automation framework

Tools:
=======
Test Design - Cucumber (Gherkin)
Test Execution - Selenium WebDriver, Java
Test Configuration - Junit
Test Report - ExtentReports
Build - Maven

From intelij:
1. Create a project in Maven
   File> New> Project> Maven

2. Open pom.xml, inside <project>, add all required libraries

3. Add a "dependencies"tag

<dependencies> </dependencies>

4. Inside the <dependencies> tag add all required libraries

Get the dependencies from Maven site
https://mvnrepository.com
  junit 4.13.1
  Selenium 3.141.59
  Cucumber JVM Java 1.2.6
  Cucumber Junit 1.2.6
  WebDriverManager 4.2.2
  extentsreports 3.1.2
  Cucumber ExtentsReport 3.1.1
Remove <type> and <scope> tags

Right click maven and click Reload Project to load the dependencies


5. Designing a Test using Cucumber
Create a
- directory in >src>test> features
- package in >test>java> stepDefinitions
- package in >main>java>pageObjects
- package in >main>java>functionLibrary
- package in >main>java>pageObjects

- dir in src>main>java>resources>errorShots
- dir in src>main>java>resources>testData

- class in test>java>RunScripts
@RunWith(Cucumber.class)
@CucumberOptions(features = ".", tags = {}, dryRun = true)
public class RunScripts {
}

- class in test>java>Hooks (to configure all common functions such as open browser, close browser)

6. Create classes in
- main>java>pageObjects>HomePage
- main>java>pageObjects>ProductsPage
etc

- pacakgage >test > stepDefinitions

7. Create features
- Create a .feature file in >test>features

 create a file with name existingUserLogin.feature

In existingUserLogin.feature tab define the test steps
Feature:    Verify existing user login

            As an existing user
            I should login to application

  Scenario: To verify Login popup is displayed
    Given   Landed on Home Page

    When    I click on Login button

    Then    I should see Login page

8. Run the RunScripts.java with dryRun=true
9. Copy the Snippets to the appropriate class in test> java> stepDefinitions